403 1271.262 1394.250 1270.142 C 1336.486 1262.747, 1273.186 1261.833, 1216.500 1267.575 C 1004.825 1289.018, 811.645 1394.647, 678.041 1562 C 600.765 1658.795, 547.067 1773.146, 522.137 1894 C 506.255 1970.993, 502.021 2055.078, 510.058 2133.902 C 532.485 2353.872, 645.695 2553.167, 824.084 2686.712 C 987.252 2808.862, 1189.714 2862.691, 1393 2837.970 C 1509.978 2823.745, 1623.296 2782.623, 1723.740 2717.949 C 1771.073 2687.472, 1810.621 2655.388, 1853.079 2613.022 C 1903.041 2563.168, 1939.608 2516.680, 1974.232 2459 C 2039.821 2349.734, 2076.849 2229.561, 2084.998 2099.517 C 2085.642 2089.246, 2086 1922.568, 2086 1633.145 L 2086 1182.756 2087.869 1184.128 C 2097.391 1191.117, 2143.163 1220.976, 2157 1229.226 C 2269.843 1296.502, 2391.394 1340.776, 2520 1361.444 C 2566.408 1368.903, 2625.602 1373.982, 2666.250 1373.995 L 2683 1374 2683 1159 L 2683 944 2670.250 943.996 C 2646.831 943.988, 2613.641 940.897, 2584.464 936.006 C 2478.567 918.253, 2380.928 872.803, 2297 802.193 C 2280.460 788.277, 2240.163 747.811, 2226.604 731.500 C 2153.177 643.171, 2108.102 541.999, 2092.054 429.500 C 2089.652 412.660, 2087.341 385.409, 2086.436 363.250 L 2085.772 347 1871.553 347 C 1753.732 347, 1657.033 347.300, 1656.667 347.667\" stroke=\"none\" fill=\"#fffcfc\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path><path d=\"\" stroke=\"none\" fill=\"#fcfcfc\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></a></div><div class=\"copyright\"><div>©<!-- -->2026<!-- --> CoinMarketCap</div></div></footer></div></div></div><script id=\"__NEXT_DATA__\" type=\"application/json\">{\"props\":{\"pageProps\":{\"article\":{\"id\":\"69c09f9a2694464654afae65\",\"title\":\"Bitcoin Stabilizes Near $70K but Traders Still Bet on the Downside, VanEck Reports\",\"slug\":\"bitcoin-stabilizes-near-dollar70k-but-traders-still-bet-on-the-downside-vaneck-reports\",\"meta\":\"Despite that stabilization, demand for options that pay out on a price decline has remained unusually high.\",\"visible\":true,\"image\":{\"original\":\"uploads/1924a9cba9da40e4b13ab1b59e4b41d9.jpg\",\"optimized\":\"optimized-uploads/1924a9cba9da40e4b13ab1b59e4b41d9.jpg\",\"thumbnail\":\"thumbnail-uploads/1924a9cba9da40e4b13ab1b59e4b41d9.jpg\"},\"content\":\"\\u003ch2 id=\\\"bitcoin-news\\\"\\u003eBitcoin News\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eBitcoin traders are paying more for downside protection than at any point on record relative to spot volume, according to a mid-March \\u003ca href=\\\"https://www.vaneck.com/us/en/blogs/digital-assets/matthew-sigel-vaneck-mid-march-2026-bitcoin-chaincheck/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\\\"\\u003ereport \\u003c/a\\u003efrom investment firm VanEck. The data shows that even as Bitcoin prices have stabilized near $70,000, investors remain heavily positioned to profit if prices fall further.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003ca href=\\\"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/bitcoin/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\\\"\\u003eBitcoin's\\u003c/a\\u003e realized volatility dropped from 80 to just above 50 over the past month. The price has held relatively steady during that period, recently trading around $69,891. Despite that stabilization, demand for options that pay out on a price decline has remained unusually high.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eTraders spent approximately $685 million on put options over the 30 days covered in VanEck's report. That figure declined 24% compared to the prior month but still ranked above 77% of all monthly observations since the start of 2025. Call option premiums fell 12% over the same period to around $562 million.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe put/call open interest ratio averaged 0.77 during the period and peaked at 0.84. VanEck said that peak is the highest level recorded since June 2021, when China moved to restrict \\u003ca href=\\\"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/bitcoin/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\\\"\\u003eBitcoin\\u003c/a\\u003e mining activity. The firm described the reading as reflecting \\\"unusually strong demand for downside hedging relative to bullish positioning.\\\"\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eRelative to spot volume, put premiums reached roughly 4 basis points, which VanEck identified as an all-time high in its dataset. That level is approximately three times higher than readings observed in mid-2022 following the Terra/Luna stablecoin collapse and the Ethereum staking liquidity crisis.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eFutures funding rates also eased during the period, falling to 2.7% from 4.1%. That decline suggests leveraged speculation has cooled alongside the drop in realized volatility.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eVanEck noted that past episodes of similarly elevated options fear have typically preceded recoveries rather than further declines. Looking back over the past six years, the firm found that comparable skew readings were followed by average\\u003ca href=\\\"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/bitcoin/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\\\"\\u003e Bitcoin\\u003c/a\\u003e gains of 13% over the next 90 days and 133% over the following 360 days.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eOn-chain activity remained weak during the review period, though miner selling showed signs of staying contained. VanEck also noted that Bitcoin transfers among holders with positions of at least one year appeared to be slowing month-over-month, suggesting long-term holders are distributing less than in previous periods.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003ca href=\\\"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/bitcoin/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\\\"\\u003eBitcoin\\u003c/a\\u003e remains approximately 45% below its all-time high of $126,080 set in October 2025.\\u003c/p\\u003e\",\"disclaimer\":\"This article contains links to third-party websites or other content for information purposes only (“Third-Party Sites”). The Third-Party Sites are not under the control of CoinMarketCap, and CoinMarketCap is not responsible for the content of any Third-Party Site, including without limitation any link contained in a Third-Party Site, or any changes or updates to a Third-Party Site. CoinMarketCap is providing these links to you only as a convenience, and the inclusion of any link does not imply endorsement, approval or recommendation by CoinMarketCap of the site or any association with its operators. This article is intended to be used and must be used for informational purposes only. It is important to do your own research and analysis before making any material decisions related to any of the products or services described. This article is not intended as, and shall not be construed as, financial advice. The views and opinions expressed in this article are the author’s [company’s] own and do not necessarily reflect those of CoinMarketCap. \\n\",\"language\":\"en\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-23T02:04:10.132Z\",\"reading_time\":94000,\"likes\":0,\"shares\":0,\"srd\":false,\"related\":[{\"id\":\"69cfce290c85346732c38d4c\",\"title\":\"Bitcoin Supply in Profit Approaches 2022 Bear Market Levels\",\"slug\":\"bitcoin-supply-in-profit-approaches-2022-bear-market-levels\",\"meta\":\" During the last bear market, Bitcoin in profit fell to approximately 9 million at its lowest point, while coins held at a loss peaked at around 10.6 million.\",\"image\":{\"original\":\"uploads/e69e73781d754bdb976365b9b6bb3d67.jpg\",\"optimized\":\"optimized-uploads/e69e73781d754bdb976365b9b6bb3d67.jpg\",\"thumbnail\":\"thumbnail-uploads/e69e73781d754bdb976365b9b6bb3d67.jpg\"},\"language\":\"en\",\"created_at\":\"2026-04-03T14:26:53.775Z\",\"reading_time\":94500,\"categories\":[{\"id\":\"686290d6c8c34339c7260b3b\",\"title\":\"CMC Crypto News\",\"description\":\"Read crypto news today and discover knowledgeable insights from leaders in the blockchain and cryptocurrency sectors.\",\"language\":\"en\",\"slug\":\"cmc-crypto-news\",\"icon\":\"https://academy-public.coinmarketcap.com/optimized-uploads/12cb7e8eb592459da5bfcd3cce391ece.png\"}],\"author\":{\"name\":\"Decentrali